        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(memory): respect QMD timeout for memory_search",
        "body": "## Summary\n- apply `memory.qmd.limits.timeoutMs` only to actual QMD-backed `memory_search` work\n- keep the existing 15s guard for manager setup, wiki/supplement-only searches, builtin searches, and QMD-to-builtin fallback paths\n- strengthen regression coverage for raised-QMD-timeout behavior across QMD search, `corpus=\"wiki\"`, and fallback searches\n- document that QMD `limits.timeoutMs` controls the QMD memory-search budget and add a manual smoke test for checking gateway/backend logs after raising the timeout\n\n## What Problem This Solves\nQMD-backed memory searches can legitimately take longer than the historical fixed 15s `memory_search` wrapper, even though the QMD config already exposes `memory.qmd.limits.timeoutMs`. The original fix made that configured timeout the whole-tool deadline too early, which also lengthened non-QMD work such as wiki-only supplement searches and builtin/fallback searches. This revision keeps the longer QMD budget scoped to live QMD-backed memory-search work while preserving the old 15s guard everywhere else.\n\n## Evidence\n- Local QMD-backed runtime evidence from the PR thread shows the pre-patch fixed 15s timeout and a post-patch QMD result completing with `searchMs: 23922` under `memory.qmd.limits.timeoutMs = 45000`.\n- Added focused fake-timer coverage proving a configured 45s QMD search is still pending and un-aborted at 15s, then aborts with `memory_search timed out after 45s`.\n- Added focused fake-timer coverage proving a QMD-configured `corpus=\"wiki\"` supplement-only call still returns `memory_search timed out after 15s` and never opens the memory manager.\n- Added focused fake-timer coverage proving a QMD-configured live builtin fallback search still returns `memory_search timed out after 15s` and aborts the search signal.\n- Local validation on this branch passed: `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 extensions/memory-core/src/tools.ts extensions/memory-core/src/tools.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory-tool-manager.test-mocks.ts`.\n- Local validation on this branch passed: `node scripts/format-docs.mjs --check docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md docs/reference/memory-config.md`.\n- Local validation on this branch passed: `node scripts/test-extension.mjs memory-core extensions/memory-core/src/tools.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/tools.citations.test.ts` with 2 files and 40 tests passing.\n- Local validation on this branch passed: `pnpm tsgo:extensions:test`.\n- Local validation on this branch passed: `node scripts/test-extension.mjs memory-core` with 63 files and 915 tests passing.\n\n## Manual smoke test\nAfter applying this branch to an installation with QMD memory enabled:\n1. Set `memory.qmd.limits.timeoutMs` above 15000, e.g. `45000`, and restart the gateway.\n2. Run `memory_search` from a tool-enabled agent session with a query known to take longer than 15s on that machine.\n3. Inspect gateway/backend logs for that search window. The old `memory_search timed out after 15s` failure should not appear for the QMD-backed search. If the search still exceeds the configured QMD budget, the unavailable payload should report the configured timeout, e.g. `memory_search timed out after 45s`.\n4. Run a wiki-only or fallback-path search under the same raised QMD timeout. Those non-QMD paths should still hit the existing 15s guard if they stall.\n\n## Tests\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 extensions/memory-core/src/tools.ts extensions/memory-core/src/tools.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory-tool-manager.test-mocks.ts`\n- `node scripts/format-docs.mjs --check docs/concepts/memory-qmd.md docs/reference/memory-config.md`\n- `node scripts/test-extension.mjs memory-core extensions/memory-core/src/tools.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/tools.citations.test.ts`\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions:test`\n- `node scripts/test-extension.mjs memory-core`\n",
        "branch": "julian/configurable-memory-search-timeout",
